quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  78,31,The triumphant finale shall belong to the pious
  78,32,The orchards and the vineyards
  78,33,And blossoming buxom belle _ (the well matched maidens) _ as mates
  78,34,And the brimful cups (of wine)
  78,35,"Inane nonsense talk and (false) gossip, they shall not hear in paradise"
  78,36,"Compensation from your Lord, a bountiful and generous grant"
  78,37,"Before Rehman _ the Lord of the heavens and the earth, and everything between them _ they won´t dare to speak"
  78,38,"On that day, all souls and all angels shall stand (before Him) in rows. No one shall dare to speak unless Rehman grants permission, and on condition that he will speak only what is proper"
  78,39,"Such is the day of the truth! (It is sure to arrive). Now, whoever wishes may seek the course towards his Lord"
  78,40,"We have certainly warned you of the (imminent and) impending doom. On that day, man would look at the deeds he had sent ahead; he would say, \"Alas! if I were only dust"